  "query": "What are the most effective ways to increase soil organic carbon on loamy soils?",
  "answer": "The most effective ways to increase soil organic carbon on loamy soils are to change tillage practices and to amend the soil with formulated chemical compounds.\n\nChanging tillage practices is a key method for managing soil organic carbon, although results can be inconsistent (ID 906). While twelve studies indicated that no-tillage or reduced tillage systems lead to higher soil organic carbon, a notable trial in Spain revealed that conventionally tilled soil actually had greater soil organic carbon. Furthermore, it's important to consider potential downsides, as some studies have shown that reduced tillage can lead to greater soil compaction. Another highly effective method is amending the soil with chemical compounds, such as nitrogen and phosphorus fertilizers, which has been shown in five out of six studies to increase soil organic matter or carbon (ID 909). In addition to soil health benefits, one study also demonstrated that increased fertilizer application can lead to higher yields for crops like maize, wheat, and rice (ID 909).",
